#EdTech Curriculum and Textbook Analysis

This project demonstrates SQL-based analysis of an EdTech publishing dataset using multiple joins to answer real-world business questions around textbook adoption, author relationships, and curriculum alignment.

The analysis focuses on connecting courses, textbooks, and authors to generate insights that could support curriculum planning and textbook sales strategy.

--

#Objective

The primary goals of this analysis were to:

-Identify current economics textbooks used in the curriculum
-Connect textbooks to their associated authors
-Analyze 12th-grade course textbook assignments
-Determine which authors are tied to upper-level course materials
-Strengthen SQL skills using multiple joins across related tables

#Business Questions

-Which current economics textbooks are being used in the curriculum?
-Which authors are associated with current economics textbooks?
-Which 12th-grade courses have assigned textbooks and authors?
-How can multiple joins connect curriculum, textbook, and author data?
-How can curriculum usage data support textbook sales strategy?

