#SQL Analysis

-1. Current Economics Textbooks and Their Authors
SELECT Textbooks.Title,
       AuthorTextbookLink.AuthorID,
       Authors.Name
FROM Textbooks
INNER JOIN AuthorTextbookLink
    ON Textbooks.TextbookID = AuthorTextbookLink.TextbookID
INNER JOIN Authors
    ON AuthorTextbookLink.AuthorID = Authors.AuthorID
WHERE Subject = 'Economics'
  AND Current = 'Yes';

Business Insight:
This query identifies current economics textbooks that are actively used and links them to authors in the company database.

Business Impact:
Supports curriculum analysis and helps sales teams focus on currently adopted economics materials and the authors behind them.

-2. 12th-Grade Courses with Textbook Titles and Author IDs
SELECT Courses.CourseName,
       Textbooks.Title,
       AuthorTextbookLink.AuthorID
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Textbooks
    ON Courses.TextbookID = Textbooks.TextbookID
LEFT JOIN AuthorTextbookLink
    ON Textbooks.TextbookID = AuthorTextbookLink.TextbookID
WHERE Courses.GradeLevel = 12;

Business Insight:
This query returns all 12th-grade courses and includes associated textbook and author information where available.

Business Impact:
Useful for curriculum audits because it preserves all 12th-grade courses, even if some do not yet have a linked textbook or author.

-3. 12th-Grade Courses with Textbooks and Author Names
SELECT Courses.CourseName,
       Textbooks.Title,
       Authors.Name
FROM Textbooks
INNER JOIN Courses
    ON Textbooks.TextbookID = Courses.TextbookID
INNER JOIN AuthorTextbookLink
    ON Textbooks.TextbookID = AuthorTextbookLink.TextbookID
INNER JOIN Authors
    ON AuthorTextbookLink.AuthorID = Authors.AuthorID
WHERE Courses.GradeLevel = 12;

Business Insight:
This query identifies 12th-grade courses that have fully matched textbook and author records.

Business Impact:
Supports clearer reporting for sales and curriculum teams by showing only complete course-textbook-author relationships.
